    "updated_at": "2025-02-19T07:35:45Z",
    "body": "Actually I know the answer \"how to make it just work\" (in my case).\n\nIt has to do with how `TERM` is defined in your environment (which in turn affects how colors are displayed in applications like neovim eg).\n\nWhat worked for me:\n\n```\n// in wezterm: ensure escape characters dont escape \nconfig.term = \"tmux-256color\"\n```\n\n```\n// in tmux: ensure colors are displayed correctly\nset-option -g terminal-overrides ',xterm-256color:Tc'\n```\n\nBut the real question is why this happens at all or in \"wrong\" TERM's like `xterm-256color` and why clear instructions on how to handle situations like this are not present\n",
    "author_association": "NONE",
